<b>(2) Matrix models -- discrete time, linear maps</b> (2 weeks)
<ul>
  <li>Introduction to population biology</li>
  <li>Euler-Lotka formula and root-finding for age-class models:
    &quot;Leslie Matrices&quot;</li>
  <li>Matrix multiplication and eigenvalues </li>
  <li>The Perron-Frobenius Theorem,
    dominant eigenvalues and population growth</li>
  <li>Eigenvalue sensitivity formulas and applications in ecology</li>
</ul>
                    
<blockquote>
  <p>READINGS: </p>
  <ul>
    <li> EG Chapter 2 <a href="materials/chap2_summary.pdf">Summary here</a></li>
    <li> Literature: <a href="materials/crouse_et_al_sea_turtles.pdf"> crouse.pdf </a></li>
  </ul>                       
